The paper presents a game-theoretic model of competition between web search algorithms and studies the impact on user welfare. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the differentiation of search results and the impact on user satisfaction, which could also place it in the Electronic Commerce (cs.EC) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
